1
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:32,020
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,970
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:37,580
Madam,

4
00:01:37,910 --> 00:01:39,190
I won't go in.

5
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,440
I...

6
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,100
I'll just wait in the courtyard.

7
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:04,990
Bastards, idiots,

8
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,030
a bunch of cowards.

9
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:07,140
Stop yelling.

10
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,770
Uncle is in the room.

11
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,490
Tell him I won't be back for a while.

12
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:14,950
Fengnian.

13
00:03:20,690 --> 00:03:21,660
Uncle.

14
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:25,070
Uncle is here.

15
00:03:27,530 --> 00:03:29,829
How is your health?

16
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,140
Pour some tea.

17
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:34,610
Fengnian, pardon my intrusion.

18
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:36,200
What are you talking about?

19
00:03:36,350 --> 00:03:38,380
I just arrived late last night.

20
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:41,820
I went straight to the barracks
early this morning for work.

21
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,100
Is everything alright

22
00:03:44,770 --> 00:03:46,370
with Yunkui?

23
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:47,460
He's fine.

24
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,620
What could have happened?

25
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:52,150
It's just that the fighting
at the front is pretty intense,

26
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:53,920
and communications keep getting cut off.

27
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,690
We are also waiting for
his latest battle report.

28
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:57,490
Division Commander Sun is back.

29
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:58,630
Fengnian,

30
00:03:59,180 --> 00:04:01,240
we've been family friends for years.

31
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:04,070
If anything has happened to Yunkui,

32
00:04:04,390 --> 00:04:06,220
you must tell me the truth.

33
00:04:08,950 --> 00:04:10,810
Uncle, please sit down.

34
00:04:11,110 --> 00:04:11,970
You go ahead.

35
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:23,420
My coffin has long been prepared.

36
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,580
I've thought about it.

37
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:29,220
If Yunkui dies heroically in battle,

38
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:31,120
let him use it first.

39
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,610
I can hold on.

40
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:34,740
Uncle Shi, don't overthink it.

41
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:37,490
I'll report to you
as soon as there is any news.

42
00:04:38,730 --> 00:04:40,740
He wrote a few days ago,

43
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:42,890
saying he was guarding
the Baijiazhai.

44
00:04:42,890 --> 00:04:43,420
Yes.

45
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,190
But, look,

46
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,340
Dachang has been lost.

47
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:47,960
Then,

48
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:50,610
has his position been lost too?

49
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:09,300
The 87th Brigade was very brave.

50
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:10,550
The whole brigade

51
00:05:12,060 --> 00:05:13,920
died heroically for the country.

52
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,150
But,

53
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,780
we haven't found Yunkui's body yet.

54
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:27,870
What does that mean?

55
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:29,630
The higher-ups' position

56
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:31,070
was that the unit should hold its ground.

57
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:32,570
But Yunkui and over 50 of his men

58
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:33,760
weren't at the position,

59
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,159
so we couldn't find them.

60
00:05:35,230 --> 00:05:36,960
It's hard to draw a conclusion.

61
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:38,300
Conclusion?

62
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,430
What conclusion?

63
00:05:46,470 --> 00:05:48,020
So you mean...

64
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:50,950
he deserted his post
and fled the battlefield?

65
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:51,380
I,

66
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:52,800
I didn't mean that.

67
00:05:52,970 --> 00:05:54,630
But Dachang is lost after all,

68
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:57,680
and the higher-ups
are holding people accountable.

69
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,440
So,

70
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:04,340
there's still a glimmer
of hope for Yunkui.

71
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:07,340
But the position was lost.

72
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:08,900
According to military law,

73
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:10,310
even if he is alive,

74
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:12,600
it's a dead end.

75
00:06:19,530 --> 00:06:20,730
Please have some tea.

76
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:25,570
I believe in Yunkui!

77
00:06:28,610 --> 00:06:30,970
You believe in him too, do you?

78
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:34,500
Uncle.

79
00:07:06,490 --> 00:07:07,160
Please!

80
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:07,910
Uncle.

81
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:08,790
Please don't.

82
00:07:08,810 --> 00:07:09,530
I believe Yunkui.

83
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:10,200
I really do.

84
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:21,610
What exactly is going on?

85
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,120
Say something.

86
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,790
Bastards, idiots,

87
00:07:25,810 --> 00:07:27,070
and a bunch of cowards!

88
00:07:27,970 --> 00:07:30,190
Not one of you is any good.

89
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:47,490
Is he injured?

90
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:52,370
Badly?

91
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,790
Which hospital is he in?

92
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:07,780
I haven't had a warm meal in days.

93
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:09,350
Thank you, Madam.

94
00:08:19,090 --> 00:08:20,580
Are you all back?

95
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:24,310
If there's something to tell,
just tell Madam.

96
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:25,180
Don't keep us in suspense.

97
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,910
You're making us worried sick.

98
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:31,520
Orders are orders; don't you understand?

99
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:51,320
Is it enough?

100
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,070
If not,

101
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,070
I'll have Mrs. Liu cook some more.

102
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:58,320
It's enough, Madam.

103
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:01,060
Well,

104
00:09:01,090 --> 00:09:01,730
Madam,

105
00:09:01,970 --> 00:09:04,100
our brigade commander's strict order

106
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:07,420
is that I can only tell Master.

107
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,130
If you don't tell me where Master is,

108
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,210
I'll go find him.

109
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,130
Otherwise, I'll go halfway

110
00:09:14,130 --> 00:09:15,490
and stop him.

111
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,400
Forget it.

112
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:21,120
I'll come back tonight.

113
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,570
Mrs. Liu!

114
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:31,760
-Give it to me!
-No, no, no!

115
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,360
Give it to me!

116
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,350
This belongs to our family!

117
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:34,100
Our young master's sword.

118
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,690
Give it to me!

119
00:09:40,540 --> 00:09:41,780
Madam.

120
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:17,450
I haven't asked;

121
00:10:18,050 --> 00:10:19,390
what's your name?

122
00:10:20,970 --> 00:10:21,570
My...

123
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,080
My name is Meng Wanfu.

124
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,940
I was the Brigade Commander's orderly.

125
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,080
Tell me your brigade commander's orders.

126
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:33,960
Word for word.

127
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,980
He said,

128
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,030
"Deliver this sword

129
00:10:41,060 --> 00:10:43,770
to my father, Zhang Ruxian,

130
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:47,590
at No. 99, Yihe Road, Nanjing.

131
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,200
Tell him

132
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:53,230
I've served my country faithfully."

133
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:58,230
Not a single word missing.

134
00:10:58,650 --> 00:11:00,180
Those were his exact words.

135
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:07,090
Alright.

136
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:13,940
Thank you for your hard work, Wanfu.

137
00:11:14,730 --> 00:11:16,960
There is one thing I'd like to ask of you.

138
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:20,510
Master is getting old,

139
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,280
and his health is not very good.

140
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,020
So don't tell him

141
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:28,710
about this.

142
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,620
I will tell him myself.

143
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,770
No, Madam.

144
00:11:32,970 --> 00:11:34,680
I swore an oath.

145
00:11:34,710 --> 00:11:37,110
I must deliver this sword...

146
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,120
Madam.

147
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:42,800
Madam.

148
00:11:45,490 --> 00:11:47,560
Madam, Master is back.

149
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:49,370
Master.

150
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:51,590
-Go.
-I know.

151
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,990
Come on, get moving.

152
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:55,300
You don't beg inside someone's home.

153
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,270
I'll go get you some food
in the front yard.

154
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:58,200
Yujiao.

155
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,670
Dad, you're back.

156
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:03,440
I saw Liao Fengnian.

157
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:05,920
Yunkui is still at the front.

158
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,740
He's fighting well,

159
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,370
but the latest war report

160
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,510
hasn't come out yet.

161
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:11,960
We have to wait for news.

162
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:13,340
Get out.

163
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,050
I'll see you out.

164
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,000
Go.

165
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:18,640
Get out.

166
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:20,060
I'm begging you, get out.

167
00:12:20,090 --> 00:12:21,160
Stop!

168
00:12:27,070 --> 00:12:27,810
Come here.

169
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:49,610
You're a soldier?

170
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:10,360
Are you from the 87th Brigade?

171
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:28,870
Father.

172
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,450
You found out?

173
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:22,770
My son fell in battle,

174
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:27,270
brave to the end—

175
00:14:35,990 --> 00:14:38,580
he met his fate with honor!

176
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:44,450
He met his fate with honor!

177
00:15:11,570 --> 00:15:13,530
Young Master.

178
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,320
Master!

179
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,590
A whole brigade

180
00:15:25,470 --> 00:15:28,910
has been wiped out!

181
00:15:30,290 --> 00:15:32,220
Young Master.

182
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,960
Young man,

183
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,570
were you at your brigade commander's side

184
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,870
when he fell?

185
00:16:03,780 --> 00:16:04,530
Yes.

186
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:11,880
Then tell me everything exactly

187
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,820
as it happened—

188
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:16,400
the whole scene, word for word!

189
00:16:30,650 --> 00:16:31,890
Don't be afraid.

190
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:33,500
Tell Deputy Division Commander Liao

191
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,730
exactly what you told me.

192
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,170
Be truthful,

193
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:39,020
and don't exaggerate.

194
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,730
Speak.

195
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:47,910
Don't worry, Uncle.

196
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:50,190
Little brother,

197
00:16:50,410 --> 00:16:51,410
tell the truth.

198
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:53,730
Just say what you saw with your own eyes.

199
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,520
Our front line was too miserable.

200
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,990
The enemy's artillery

201
00:17:05,569 --> 00:17:06,920
never stopped—

202
00:17:07,369 --> 00:17:08,579
daytime bombardments,

203
00:17:08,579 --> 00:17:10,740
then nighttime bombardments.

204
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,329
Our trenches were full of water.

205
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,010
We were soaking in that water

206
00:17:16,010 --> 00:17:17,450
all day long.

207
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,030
Talk about Zhang Yunkui.

208
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:21,089
Yes.

209
00:17:21,589 --> 00:17:23,839
Our brigade commander

210
00:17:24,010 --> 00:17:25,359
was simply amazing.

211
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,109
He ordered his men

212
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:28,670
to use mortars

213
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,270
and machine...

214
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:31,410
Machine‑gun nests.

215
00:17:31,410 --> 00:17:32,670
Yes, machine gun nests

216
00:17:32,770 --> 00:17:34,030
and even hand grenades

217
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:37,120
to attack the enemy's po‑po positions.

218
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,070
Mortar positions.

219
00:17:38,070 --> 00:17:39,460
That's right. Mortar positions.

220
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:40,530
Anyway, they repelled

221
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:42,680
batch after batch of the Japanese.

222
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:43,810
Our brigade commander

223
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:46,040
predicted things like a god,

224
00:17:46,150 --> 00:17:47,330
just like Zhuge Liang.

225
00:17:47,330 --> 00:17:48,200
See?

226
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:50,160
Yunkui was just like this.

227
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:52,460
He was a qualified soldier.

228
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:53,590
Yes.

229
00:17:54,350 --> 00:17:55,830
Go on.

230
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:59,050
Anyway, defending Baijiazhai

231
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:00,880
was very hard.

232
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,120
I remember

233
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:04,430
it was the night
of the Mid-Autumn Festival.

234
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:05,730
There were only

235
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,920
over 400 brothers left on our position.

236
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,940
The Brigade Commander said

237
00:18:08,940 --> 00:18:11,510
the higher-ups asked us
to hold out for another 3 days.

238
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:13,420
But half of our brothers

239
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:15,090
would die in one day.

240
00:18:15,310 --> 00:18:17,620
There weren't enough people
to die for 3 days.

241
00:18:17,620 --> 00:18:18,550
We heard long ago

242
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:20,220
that there would be reinforcements
from Liu Town

243
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:21,370
to support us,

244
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:23,000
but day after day,

245
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:25,110
there was no sign of them.

246
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,380
The Brigade Commander said

247
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,240
we should move to meet the reinforcements—

248
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,210
but we couldn't leave our position.

249
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:32,580
And our phone line
to the Division Headquarters was cut.

250
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:34,430
Everyone argued endlessly.

251
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:36,830
Our brigade commander
was also extremely anxious.

252
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:38,330
I made water caltrop mooncakes

253
00:18:38,330 --> 00:18:39,860
for our brigade commander.

254
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,600
He didn't have much of an appetite,

255
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:44,500
but he still praised me:

256
00:18:44,530 --> 00:18:45,660
"At a time like this,

257
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,510
you find a way

258
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:49,260
to make mooncakes for everyone
during Mid-Autumn—

259
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:51,500
you've honored the name of the Chinese."

260
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,450
Cut to the important part.

261
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,320
Master, what is not important?

262
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:56,580
Skip to the later part.

263
00:18:56,610 --> 00:18:57,350
There's no rest

264
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:58,680
without the beginning.

265
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:02,320
Tell us.

266
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:04,520
That night...

267
00:19:05,140 --> 00:19:06,420
the Brigade Commander
was on his night patrol.

268
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:08,870
I handed out mooncakes
to everyone with him.

269
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:10,030
But as we walked,

270
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:11,670
he suddenly stopped

271
00:19:11,830 --> 00:19:13,070
and told the men:

272
00:19:13,210 --> 00:19:14,130
"Brothers,

273
00:19:14,330 --> 00:19:17,000
this is a position we built ourselves.

274
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:18,680
We will guard it ourselves

275
00:19:18,830 --> 00:19:19,960
and never retreat."

276
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:21,090
Actually,

277
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,320
these were the words of
Platoon Leader Wang, who had died.

278
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,620
I didn't understand at the time

279
00:19:25,620 --> 00:19:26,640
why the Brigade Commander would repeat

280
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,970
Platoon Leader Wang's words.

281
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,340
-After that…
-Young man,

282
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:31,330
it doesn't matter
what Platoon Leader Wang said.

283
00:19:31,330 --> 00:19:32,650
What did your brigade commander say?

284
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:33,360
Yeah.

285
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:35,300
I...

286
00:19:35,330 --> 00:19:37,330
Right, our brigade commander said,

287
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:38,770
"Brothers,

288
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,790
I will absolutely not

289
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:41,660
let you die in vain again."

290
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:42,630
After saying that,

291
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:44,610
our brigade commander led 50 people

292
00:19:44,610 --> 00:19:46,780
as a suicide squad and set off.

293
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:52,130
So that's how you
ended up going to Liu Town?

294
00:19:52,370 --> 00:19:54,220
Our brigade commander
wanted to take care of me,

295
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:55,490
so he told me not to go

296
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:56,800
and let me go home.

297
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,230
Could I leave?

298
00:19:58,660 --> 00:19:59,710
I couldn't.

299
00:20:00,170 --> 00:20:02,200
I wanted to be with my brothers.

300
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,590
I volunteered for the suicide squad.

301
00:20:04,610 --> 00:20:05,700
I wanted to go with them

302
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:06,890
to bring reinforcements back

303
00:20:06,890 --> 00:20:08,740
within a day and a night.

304
00:20:11,130 --> 00:20:12,780
Are you guys wondering

305
00:20:12,810 --> 00:20:14,200
why I stayed

306
00:20:14,230 --> 00:20:16,090
and why I didn't leave?

307
00:20:17,530 --> 00:20:18,480
Let me tell you.

308
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,350
It's because

309
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:21,110
I fought a bloody battle alongside

310
00:20:21,110 --> 00:20:23,230
the brothers of the 87th Brigade.

311
00:20:23,310 --> 00:20:24,290
You don't know

312
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:26,590
how fierce and brutal

313
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:27,630
the battle at Baijiazhai was.

314
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:30,170
The machine guns rattled

315
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:32,490
the automatic rifles cracked

316
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,510
and grenades exploded—

317
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:35,070
boom, boom, boom!

318
00:20:35,220 --> 00:20:36,340
Especially our brigade commander,

319
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:37,390
he took the mortar

320
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,000
and aimed it at the charging
Japanese soldiers,

321
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,860
one shot, two shots, three shots—

322
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:45,310
boom, crash, bang!

323
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:48,130
The whole position

324
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:50,950
went quiet.

325
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,240
We won.

326
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,640
Have some water.

327
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:01,250
Listen,

328
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,580
this is the real battle situation.

329
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,760
I know exactly what happened
at Baijiazhai.

330
00:21:06,930 --> 00:21:08,660
When did you arrive at Liu Town?

331
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,760
Sir,

332
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:13,790
early the next morning,

333
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:15,850
we arrived at Liu Town.

334
00:21:15,940 --> 00:21:17,400
But when we got to Liu Town,

335
00:21:17,890 --> 00:21:19,160
there was no one there—

336
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,030
none of the 159th Division,

337
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:21,790
not a soul.

338
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,790
A bunch of us idiots

339
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:25,940
rushed there

340
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:27,680
only to find out

341
00:21:27,710 --> 00:21:29,840
the reinforcements had already fled.

342
00:21:30,150 --> 00:21:30,940
The brigade commander said,

343
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:32,890
"Let's quickly retreat to Baijiazhai."

344
00:21:32,890 --> 00:21:34,180
Before he could finish,

345
00:21:34,180 --> 00:21:35,900
the Japanese main force

346
00:21:37,570 --> 00:21:38,690
advanced on us.

347
00:21:39,930 --> 00:21:41,530
Our brigade commander said,

348
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:43,540
"The fortifications here are strong.

349
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:44,520
We can't go back.

350
00:21:45,250 --> 00:21:46,690
We'll fight them here.

351
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,160
We'll die here if we must.

352
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:50,770
Brothers,

353
00:21:51,970 --> 00:21:53,770
if we die, we die together."

354
00:21:55,350 --> 00:21:58,020
Our brigade commander wanted
to leave me behind

355
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:00,790
to watch them die.

356
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:03,120
But he also said,

357
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:05,180
"You have to survive.

358
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:09,170
If you make it through,

359
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,180
carry our name

360
00:22:11,210 --> 00:22:12,690
with honor.

361
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,990
Tell everyone—Chinese soldiers

362
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:18,660
face the enemy to the last,

363
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,830
not a single man retreats,

364
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:22,530
not one coward."

365
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:24,790
That day,

366
00:22:25,530 --> 00:22:26,820
we fought from morning

367
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,990
till late afternoon.

368
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,510
I watched them—

369
00:22:34,530 --> 00:22:36,970
one by one—fall in battle.

370
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,210
Staff Officer Xie.

371
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:41,300
Adjutant Zhao.

372
00:22:43,330 --> 00:22:44,380
Blindy Huang.

373
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:46,120
Xiu.

374
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:47,750
Tieta.

375
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:50,300
And the Brigade Commander.

376
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:55,380
They really all died

377
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,640
right in front of my eyes, one by one.

378
00:22:58,430 --> 00:22:59,990
Even now,

379
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:02,960
I see their faces in my dreams.

380
00:23:21,980 --> 00:23:22,860
Uncle.

381
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:30,830
My son, Yunkui...

382
00:23:32,660 --> 00:23:34,680
My son, Yunkui

383
00:23:37,030 --> 00:23:39,450
died for his country.

384
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:44,750
His loyalty is clear as the sun and moon.

385
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,360
You died a worthy death.

386
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:51,440
My son died a worthy death.

387
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,150
Young man,

388
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:08,790
you're a true comrade

389
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,920
to my son.

390
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,190
Master,

391
00:24:13,730 --> 00:24:15,220
I am the Brigade Commander.

392
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:16,890
Even if he has fallen,

393
00:24:17,140 --> 00:24:18,790
I am still his soldier!

394
00:24:18,810 --> 00:24:19,530
Yes!

395
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,570
You will always be his soldier,

396
00:24:21,620 --> 00:24:24,460
and his comrade.

397
00:24:24,790 --> 00:24:25,870
You...

398
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:32,930
Uncle, this matter is of great importance.

399
00:24:33,250 --> 00:24:35,100
I must report it
to my superiors immediately.

400
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,230
Fengnian,

401
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:37,600
given our relationship,

402
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,400
let's not talk about this.

403
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,300
Yunkui's posthumous reputation

404
00:24:43,530 --> 00:24:45,020
depends entirely on you.

405
00:24:46,050 --> 00:24:46,940
Uncle,

406
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:49,460
Yunkui and I were like brothers.

407
00:24:50,090 --> 00:24:51,780
This matter is of great importance.

408
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:53,020
It's my duty.

409
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,910
Please.

410
00:24:55,250 --> 00:24:58,070
Uncle, please accept my condolences.

411
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,670
Go back and rest early.

412
00:24:59,670 --> 00:25:01,530
I'll draft the report right away.

413
00:25:02,260 --> 00:25:04,850
Young man, let's go.

414
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,070
Wait.

415
00:25:13,370 --> 00:25:14,120
He stays.

416
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:21,340
China will prevail!

417
00:25:21,370 --> 00:25:22,830
The fate of the nation

418
00:25:22,850 --> 00:25:24,320
is decided in this battle!

419
00:25:24,350 --> 00:25:25,940
Defeat the invaders!

420
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,460
China will prevail!

421
00:25:27,490 --> 00:25:28,930
The fate of the nation

422
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:30,420
is decided in this battle!

423
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,790
Defeat the invaders!

424
00:25:31,810 --> 00:25:33,620
China will prevail!

425
00:25:35,050 --> 00:25:35,980
Sir,

426
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:37,610
where are we going?

427
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:41,100
The military camp.

428
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:43,750
What's your name?

429
00:25:43,950 --> 00:25:45,150
My name is Kong Erbao.

430
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:46,890
When did you join the army?

431
00:25:46,890 --> 00:25:47,570
The fate of the nation

432
00:25:47,570 --> 00:25:49,060
is decided in this battle!

433
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:50,600
Defeat the invaders!

434
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,060
China will prevail!

435
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:53,290
The fate of the nation

436
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:54,840
is decided in this battle!

437
00:25:54,870 --> 00:25:56,380
Defeat the invaders!

438
00:25:56,410 --> 00:25:57,560
China will prevail!

439
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:59,390
How long have you been a soldier?

440
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,700
is decided in this battle!

441
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,140
Defeat the invaders!

442
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:04,360
Sir,

443
00:26:04,380 --> 00:26:05,550
you want the truth?

444
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:10,370
I was conscripted

445
00:26:10,580 --> 00:26:11,750
on August 13th.

446
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:14,930
Sir,

447
00:26:15,130 --> 00:26:17,340
our brigade commander
told me to stay behind,

448
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:19,280
to watch them die one by one.

449
00:26:19,310 --> 00:26:21,250
I thought he was just saying it
out of anger.

450
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:22,310
But I didn't expect

451
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,270
to actually see them

452
00:26:24,300 --> 00:26:25,470
die one by one.

453
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:26,350
Sir,

454
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,640
our brigade commander said

455
00:26:27,640 --> 00:26:29,060
he wanted me to live.

456
00:26:29,090 --> 00:26:30,620
But I didn't expect him

457
00:26:31,090 --> 00:26:32,370
to trade his life

458
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,120
for mine.

459
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:36,920
Enough.

460
00:26:37,740 --> 00:26:40,140
Did you see your brigade commander's body?

461
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,130
Did you see it with your own eyes?

462
00:26:42,130 --> 00:26:43,300
When he told me to go,

463
00:26:43,330 --> 00:26:44,730
I looked back.

464
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,240
He...

465
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:47,580
He was blown up.

466
00:27:21,930 --> 00:27:22,930
Get out of the car!

467
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:37,370
Where are we going, sir?

468
00:27:39,130 --> 00:27:39,850
Take this.

469
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,040
What does this mean, sir?

470
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:45,320
Leave Nanjing.

471
00:27:46,010 --> 00:27:47,180
Don't meet your Brigade Commander's family

472
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:47,860
ever again.

473
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:48,920
Why?

474
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,520
Don't I have to testify
for the Brigade Commander?

475
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:52,260
You are a deserter.

476
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:53,410
Can your words be taken as evidence?

477
00:27:53,410 --> 00:27:54,940
Wait, what do you mean, sir?

478
00:27:54,950 --> 00:27:56,280
You are just a deserter.

479
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:57,520
I could shoot you right now.

480
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:58,840
I didn't desert.

481
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,420
The Brigade Commander asked me to leave!

482
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:01,610
Didn't I explain it to you clearly

483
00:28:01,610 --> 00:28:03,270
in front of Master?

484
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:04,490
You can't...

485
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:53,220
♪ Only iron and blood ♪

486
00:28:53,250 --> 00:28:56,810
♪ Only iron blood can save China ♪

487
00:28:57,130 --> 00:29:00,060
♪ We shall reclaim our Land and destroy the invaders ♪

488
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:02,970
♪ Awaken our nation, pledge to avenge ♪

489
00:29:03,030 --> 00:29:06,900
♪ The wind howls, the rain beats ♪

490
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,810
♪ Floods strike southwest ♪

491
00:29:08,840 --> 00:29:10,620
♪ Beast devours the northeast ♪

492
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:13,630
♪ I can't contain the rage inside ♪

493
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:16,570
♪ I can't contain the fire in my heart ♪

494
00:29:16,590 --> 00:29:18,420
♪ Rise, rise ♪

495
00:29:18,450 --> 00:29:20,300
♪ United we stand ♪

496
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:23,720
♪ Fight hard, fight hard against the thieves ♪

497
00:29:24,090 --> 00:29:28,070
♪ Only iron and blood ♪

498
00:29:28,190 --> 00:29:31,930
♪ Only iron blood can save China ♪

499
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:34,930
♪ We shall reclaim our Land and destroy the invaders ♪

500
