00:30:02,930 --> 00:30:06,700
♪ Only iron blood can save China ♪

511
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:09,960
♪ We shall reclaim our Land and destroy the invaders ♪

512
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:12,830
♪ Awaken our nation, pledge to avenge ♪

513
00:30:12,850 --> 00:30:16,720
♪ The wind howls, the rain beats ♪

514
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:18,610
♪ Floods strike southwest ♪

515
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,540
♪ Beast devours the northeast ♪

516
00:30:20,570 --> 00:30:23,480
♪ I can't contain the rage inside ♪

517
00:30:24,190 --> 00:30:27,870
[Shanghai Field Hospital]

518
00:30:25,410 --> 00:30:27,580
Sir, I can bandage them.

519
00:30:28,010 --> 00:30:30,170
Sir, let me in!

520
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:30,800
I am a doctor.

521
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:32,910
My family's been in medicine
for 4 generations!

522
00:30:32,910 --> 00:30:34,760
Make way, step aside!

523
00:30:34,780 --> 00:30:35,900
Severely wounded!

524
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,180
[Chengren High School]

525
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,400
Right away!

526
00:30:38,220 --> 00:30:39,400
[Help needed to support the troops]

527
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:39,990
Hold on, we're almost there!

528
00:30:39,450 --> 00:30:39,650
[Chengren High School]

529
00:30:40,020 --> 00:30:41,690
Doctor!

530
00:30:45,940 --> 00:30:47,900
Doctor, come here quickly!

531
00:30:47,930 --> 00:30:49,410
Hurry, heavy bleeding!

532
00:30:51,340 --> 00:30:52,820
Step aside!

533
00:30:56,330 --> 00:30:58,210
Everyone, make way!

534
00:30:58,240 --> 00:30:59,990
You can't just walk into a field hospital.

535
00:30:59,990 --> 00:31:01,270
No entry!

536
00:31:01,320 --> 00:31:01,950
Gently.

537
00:31:08,660 --> 00:31:10,510
Slow down.

538
00:31:15,670 --> 00:31:17,150
Sir, I can carry water

539
00:31:17,170 --> 00:31:18,240
and carry stretchers.

540
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,320
I can help.

541
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:20,600
Just put him here.

542
00:31:21,180 --> 00:31:22,300
Whether he lives or dies

543
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:23,620
depends on his fate.

544
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:24,530
Let's go.

545
00:31:34,250 --> 00:31:35,010
Doctor.

546
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:40,780
He's hurt so badly.

547
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:43,470
Looks like blast trauma.

548
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:45,400
Why was it delayed for so long?

549
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:46,390
Which unit brought him?

550
00:31:46,390 --> 00:31:47,120
I don't know.

551
00:31:47,130 --> 00:31:48,180
He was thrown at the door—

552
00:31:48,180 --> 00:31:49,840
didn't even have a stretcher.

553
00:31:51,390 --> 00:31:52,800
Stretcher, stretcher!

554
00:32:30,830 --> 00:32:31,780
Brother Yunkui?

555
00:32:57,310 --> 00:32:58,030
Dad,

556
00:32:58,790 --> 00:33:00,030
I'm worried.

557
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,060
Wanfu still isn't back this late.

558
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:04,470
Why on earth did

559
00:33:04,490 --> 00:33:05,820
Liao Fengnian keep him here?

560
00:33:05,820 --> 00:33:06,900
Well,

561
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:10,130
since Liao Fengnian agreed,

562
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,210
he will definitely do his best.

563
00:33:12,850 --> 00:33:14,410
We should trust him.

564
00:33:45,050 --> 00:33:48,940
[Nanjing; Pier]

565
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:47,420
Wontons! Soup dumplings!

566
00:33:47,850 --> 00:33:49,150
Spiced boiled eggs!

567
00:33:52,750 --> 00:33:53,350
Hurry.

568
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:57,690
You're in the way.

569
00:33:57,690 --> 00:33:58,300
Excuse me.

570
00:34:07,250 --> 00:34:08,670
Tickets to Wuhan are available!

571
00:34:08,540 --> 00:34:11,750
[Hankou] [Shanghai]

572
00:34:08,900 --> 00:34:10,230
Tickets are available!

573
00:34:10,409 --> 00:34:11,480
Wuhan!

574
00:34:12,929 --> 00:34:14,020
Who stepped on me?

575
00:34:14,219 --> 00:34:15,760
[Hankou] [Shanghai]

576
00:34:14,710 --> 00:34:15,510
Don't push!

577
00:34:16,350 --> 00:34:18,620
Three tickets to Wuhan, just three!

578
00:34:18,820 --> 00:34:21,010
I just need one, one to Wuhan!

579
00:34:21,070 --> 00:34:21,960
Stop pushing!

580
00:34:21,980 --> 00:34:23,120
Stop yelling!

581
00:34:23,139 --> 00:34:24,449
We're in line!

582
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:25,810
Stop pushing!

583
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:26,770
Who stepped on you?

584
00:34:26,770 --> 00:34:28,730
-Get in line!
-Take one for me. Thank you!

585
00:34:28,730 --> 00:34:30,440
Who's gonna buy one
for you? We all need tickets!

586
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,239
Stop yelling! We're all in line!

587
00:34:33,460 --> 00:34:35,270
One for me!

588
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,590
Don't push!

589
00:34:37,590 --> 00:34:39,320
One to Wuhan!

590
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:41,550
Two to Wuhan!

591
00:34:46,590 --> 00:34:47,330
Who cut in line?

592
00:34:47,330 --> 00:34:48,469
I was just here!

593
00:34:48,489 --> 00:34:49,530
Move!

594
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:50,670
To Wuhan!

595
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:52,940
How much to Wuhan?

596
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:53,800
Sold out.

597
00:34:55,090 --> 00:34:56,230
You think you're right to cut in line?

598
00:34:56,230 --> 00:34:57,980
What? It's only been a few minutes—
how are they already gone?

599
00:34:57,980 --> 00:34:59,480
Move!

600
00:34:59,860 --> 00:35:00,970
What about tomorrow's?

601
00:35:00,970 --> 00:35:01,430
Tomorrow's?

602
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:02,210
None.

603
00:35:02,230 --> 00:35:04,640
All tickets for Hankou are sold out—
sales closed!

604
00:35:04,640 --> 00:35:05,380
The day after tomorrow?

605
00:35:05,380 --> 00:35:07,160
Any day is fine.

606
00:35:07,190 --> 00:35:08,900
Come line up early tomorrow.

607
00:35:14,740 --> 00:35:16,400
Stop pushing!

608
00:35:16,710 --> 00:35:17,580
No tickets left!

609
00:35:17,580 --> 00:35:18,410
You're cutting in line again?

610
00:35:18,410 --> 00:35:19,300
Any luck getting in front?

611
00:35:19,300 --> 00:35:19,890
None of your business!

612
00:35:19,890 --> 00:35:20,320
Did you get one?

613
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:21,160
Sold out.

614
00:35:21,430 --> 00:35:22,790
What a waste of time.

615
00:35:37,890 --> 00:35:40,050
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.

616
00:35:40,270 --> 00:35:42,730
Do you know
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade?

617
00:35:43,220 --> 00:35:45,550
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.

618
00:35:46,850 --> 00:35:49,310
Do you know
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade?

619
00:35:51,210 --> 00:35:53,170
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.

620
00:36:09,180 --> 00:36:14,620
[Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.]

621
00:36:20,410 --> 00:36:25,830
[Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.]

622
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:29,230
Meng Wanfu from the 87th Brigade.

623
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:34,340
What will this child do?

624
00:36:35,950 --> 00:36:37,520
Yujiao,

625
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:39,700
what will you do?

626
00:36:39,930 --> 00:36:42,020
Sister-in-law, please don't cry.

627
00:36:42,570 --> 00:36:43,730
If you keep crying,

628
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,930
I won't be able to hold it in either.

629
00:36:48,030 --> 00:36:49,070
Liao Fengnian,

630
00:36:49,330 --> 00:36:50,300
come out!

631
00:36:50,330 --> 00:36:52,130
Yujiao has been here for a while.

632
00:36:57,570 --> 00:36:58,520
Yujiao is here.

633
00:36:59,570 --> 00:37:00,400
Brother Liao,

634
00:37:00,810 --> 00:37:02,030
did you take the soldier from yesterday

635
00:37:02,030 --> 00:37:03,900
to see your superiors?

636
00:37:04,110 --> 00:37:04,700
Yes.

637
00:37:06,150 --> 00:37:07,470
What did they say?

638
00:37:08,270 --> 00:37:09,590
No clear answer.

639
00:37:10,250 --> 00:37:11,400
What do you mean?

640
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:14,190
It's quite complicated.

641
00:37:14,210 --> 00:37:15,670
Come, Yujiao, take a seat.

642
00:37:20,230 --> 00:37:22,760
The superiors
haven't made a clear decision.

643
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:25,640
I can't really say much.

644
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,260
But you need to prepare yourself.

645
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:29,870
Prepare for what?

646
00:37:31,150 --> 00:37:33,010
It's just our

647
00:37:33,470 --> 00:37:34,950
damn rule.

648
00:37:35,290 --> 00:37:37,420
If a man dies on the battlefield,

649
00:37:37,710 --> 00:37:38,880
he died for the country.

650
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,850
If he doesn't die on the battlefield,

651
00:37:40,850 --> 00:37:42,120
it's desertion.

652
00:37:44,330 --> 00:37:46,140
Desertion?

653
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:55,460
You...

654
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,350
Are your Theater,

655
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:02,730
Corps, Division, and Army commanders

656
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:04,760
the ones labeling Yunkui like this?

657
00:38:07,580 --> 00:38:10,050
You want to make him your scapegoat?

658
00:38:17,450 --> 00:38:18,710
Where is that soldier?

659
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:20,670
Give that soldier to me.

660
00:38:20,710 --> 00:38:22,070
I'll take him to
see your commanding officer.

661
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:23,020
I'll go talk to them.

662
00:38:23,020 --> 00:38:25,020
It's useless no matter who you go to.

663
00:38:25,140 --> 00:38:26,760
I've tried finding people
and arguing with them.

664
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,840
I even fell out
with our army and division commanders.

665
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:29,730
It didn't help

666
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:30,840
Yunkui one bit.

667
00:38:32,430 --> 00:38:34,210
Look at how the Battle of Shanghai
turned out.

668
00:38:34,210 --> 00:38:35,120
From the Chairman

669
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,440
down to the Theater Commander,

670
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,070
Division Commander and Army Commander—

671
00:38:37,070 --> 00:38:38,170
who isn't responsible?

672
00:38:38,170 --> 00:38:39,740
Bringing up Yunkui now

673
00:38:40,060 --> 00:38:41,490
won't change a thing.

674
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:45,070
Nanjing is in grave danger now.

675
00:38:45,420 --> 00:38:47,420
It's not like what the newspapers say.

676
00:38:47,420 --> 00:38:48,000
You know

677
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:49,050
about Master's health

678
00:38:49,050 --> 00:38:49,910
and his temper.

679
00:38:50,510 --> 00:38:51,710
Take my advice.

680
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,880
Leave Nanjing

681
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:55,610
as soon as you can.

682
00:38:58,550 --> 00:38:59,720
Yujiao,

683
00:38:59,810 --> 00:39:01,580
I, Liao Fengnian, right to your face,

684
00:39:01,580 --> 00:39:02,620
swear to you

685
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:06,600
that I will definitely
overturn Yunkui's case in this lifetime.

686
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:09,660
Overturn the case?

687
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:13,580
This matter has already been settled?

688
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:18,560
Where is that soldier?

689
00:39:19,230 --> 00:39:20,990
He promised to return to
our house yesterday.

690
00:39:20,990 --> 00:39:23,250
We waited all night but he didn't show up.

691
00:39:23,620 --> 00:39:25,060
Where did you take him?

692
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:29,400
Liao,

693
00:39:29,770 --> 00:39:31,220
look me in the eye.

694
00:39:34,660 --> 00:39:36,370
When Yunkui and I got married,

695
00:39:37,190 --> 00:39:39,160
you were our witness.

696
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:40,920
We also agreed that

697
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,550
after our child was born,

698
00:39:42,570 --> 00:39:44,430
he would call you and your wife

699
00:39:44,450 --> 00:39:46,330
his godfather and godmother.

700
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:49,480
That soldier crawled out

701
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:50,760
from a pile of corpses.

702
00:39:51,810 --> 00:39:53,070
He walked to Nanjing

703
00:39:53,070 --> 00:39:54,350
like a ghost, step by step,

704
00:39:54,350 --> 00:39:55,660
just to hand Yunkui's sword

705
00:39:55,660 --> 00:39:57,450
to me personally.

706
00:39:58,490 --> 00:40:00,010
He was Yunkui's soldier,

707
00:40:00,310 --> 00:40:02,630
so he is my brother.

708
00:40:03,510 --> 00:40:05,760
Liao, you are also Yunkui's best friend.

709
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,170
You were comrades in arms,

710
00:40:07,170 --> 00:40:08,560
brothers who would die for each other.

711
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:09,800
Publicly or privately,

712
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:12,130
you should tell me where

713
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,480
that soldier is.

714
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:15,750
Liao Fengnian, say something!

715
00:40:17,170 --> 00:40:17,980
Yujiao,

716
00:40:19,580 --> 00:40:20,780
let me put it this way.

717
00:40:21,150 --> 00:40:22,220
Someone wants this soldier

718
00:40:22,220 --> 00:40:24,550
to completely disappear from this world.

719
00:40:26,870 --> 00:40:29,240
You want to silence him

720
00:40:30,890 --> 00:40:32,700
just to save your face,

721
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,230
to shirk responsibility

722
00:40:34,230 --> 00:40:36,180
for your failure on the battlefield,

723
00:40:36,180 --> 00:40:37,470
so you want to shift the blame

724
00:40:37,470 --> 00:40:40,220
onto a group of people
who died on the battlefield

725
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:41,980
and couldn't speak for themselves?

726
00:40:41,980 --> 00:40:44,060
How dare you!

727
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:49,660
What kind of people are you?

728
00:40:49,860 --> 00:40:51,610
What kind of army is this?

729
00:40:51,630 --> 00:40:53,860
What kind of country is this?

730
00:40:54,700 --> 00:40:57,830
Yunkui's body is still in Dachang!

731
00:40:57,970 --> 00:40:58,890
Come here.

732
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:00,980
His body is still in Dachang!

733
00:41:01,010 --> 00:41:02,080
His bones aren't even cold yet.

734
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:05,350
Do you dare to shout toward Dachang,

735
00:41:05,380 --> 00:41:06,770
"Zhang Yunkui"?

736
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:11,400
Do you dare to shout toward Dachang,

737
00:41:11,420 --> 00:41:13,380
"87th Brigade"?

738
00:41:17,900 --> 00:41:19,010
I let him go.

739
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:21,100
He left through Yijiang Gate.

740
00:41:21,450 --> 00:41:23,310
He should be out of Nanjing by now.

741
00:41:29,340 --> 00:41:31,260
What have you done?

742
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:42,160
Hello, sir,

743
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:42,800
please donate for the war effort.

744
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,260
Could you donate a little?

745
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:46,070
Sir.

746
00:41:46,090 --> 00:41:47,360
-Fight against the Japanese!
-Sir!

747
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:48,670
Everyone is responsible
for resisting the Japanese.

748
00:41:48,670 --> 00:41:49,500
Sir!

749
00:41:49,530 --> 00:41:51,940
Spiced boiled eggs!

750
00:42:01,300 --> 00:42:02,090
To Wuhan.

751
00:42:04,190 --> 00:42:05,480
It's useless to come early.

752
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:06,880
There are no tickets at the counter.

753
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,650
The scalpers bought them all.

754
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,770
Brother,

755
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:14,310
what's a scalper?

756
00:42:14,330 --> 00:42:15,990
People who sell tickets
at high prices.

757
00:42:15,990 --> 00:42:17,650
How much is a ticket from them?

758
00:42:20,450 --> 00:42:22,020
How much is this?

759
00:42:22,050 --> 00:42:23,580
One small gold bar.

760
00:42:23,600 --> 00:42:24,370
What?

761
00:42:25,070 --> 00:42:26,660
One gold bar for one ticket?

762
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:28,180
Are they crazy?

763
00:42:29,650 --> 00:42:30,870
Not to mention cabin tickets,

764
00:42:30,870 --> 00:42:31,910
even cargo hold tickets

765
00:42:31,910 --> 00:42:33,110
have skyrocketed.

766
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:34,530
Look.

767
00:42:34,550 --> 00:42:35,530
Everyone is bringing their families

768
00:42:35,530 --> 00:42:36,770
to flee to Wuhan.

769
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:38,230
Please donate for the war effort.

770
00:42:38,230 --> 00:42:39,660
Everyone,
please donate for the war effort.

771
00:42:39,660 --> 00:42:40,730
Excuse me,

772
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:44,050
do you guys want to
donate anything for the war?

773
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:45,870
Thank you very much.

774
00:42:45,890 --> 00:42:46,730
God bless you.

775
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,820
Have a nice day.

776
00:42:51,710 --> 00:42:52,840
A couple of days ago,

777
00:42:53,300 --> 00:42:55,230
the boats didn't even dare to dock.

778
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:56,220
And now,

779
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:58,150
even taking a rowboat
to the middle of the river

780
00:42:58,150 --> 00:42:59,710
costs 30 dollars.

781
00:42:59,730 --> 00:43:01,110
30 dollars?

782
00:43:01,740 --> 00:43:02,450
Isn't that almost

783
00:43:02,450 --> 00:43:03,370
a gold bar?
